<subSubSection id="1FE5655FFFE0416DCA81ED53FAA3251C" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81ED53FC56243F" blockId="22.[151,1437,978,1402]" box="[199,996,1087,1114]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCA81ED53FEE1243C" bold="true" box="[199,339,1087,1113]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">References:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DCB1CED53FDBF243C" author="Grzeschik, K. - H." box="[346,525,1087,1113]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="46 - 144" refId="ref16393" refString="Grzeschik, K. - H. (1969) On the systematics, biology and ethology of Eugaster Serville (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae). Form and Function, 1, 46 - 144." type="journal article" year="1969">Grzeschik 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE0416DC85EED2CFD2E243C" author="Hemp, C." box="[536,668,1087,1114]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" refId="ref16956" refString="Hemp, C. (2021) A Field Guide to the Bushcrickets, Wetas and Raspy Crickets of Tanzania and Kenya. Senckenberg Gesellschaft fur Naturforschung, Frankfurt, 451 pp." type="book" year="2021">Hemp 2021</bibRefCitation>
(all to nominate subspecies).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81ED0FFE2D248C" blockId="22.[151,1437,978,1402]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCA81ED0FFED02418" bold="true" box="[199,354,1123,1149]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Bioacoustics.</emphasis>
Tegmina (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DCB91ED0FFDAA2418" box="[471,536,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[161,1415,290,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-72@5.[151,1436,273,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left male tegmina of Acanthoplus discoidalis (CH8946), Acanthoproctus cervinus (CH8947), Hetrodes pupus (CHelb8948), Enyaliopsis bloyeti (CH8853), E. carolinus (CH8625), E. ephippiatus (CH7737), E. jennae (damaged; CH8267), Gymnoproctus rammei (CH8763), Eugasteroides loricatus (CH7352), Spalacomimus stettinenesis, S. talpa (CH7354), S. verruciferus (CH7188). Scale 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392715/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and the spectrum of the song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DC934ED0FFC06241B" box="[882,948,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,201,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[151,1436,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Power spectra of male calling songs in Hetrodini species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392725/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) do not show large differences to the typical 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE0416DCAD1EDEBFEB024C4" authorityName=", Kowalski &amp; Lakes-Harlan" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,258,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hetrodini">Hetrodini</taxonomicName>
pattern. However, the stridulatory file (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DC884EDEBFCAA24C4" box="[706,792,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1148,1172]" captionTargetBox="[306,1281,309,1124]" captionTargetId="figure-102@6.[306,1281,309,1124]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stridulatory files on the underside of the left tegmen (wing articulation at the right) of A Acanthoplus discoidalis (CH8946), B Cosmoderus femoralis (CH8627), C Eugasteroides loricatus (CH7352), D Spalacomimus talpa (CH7354). Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392719/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) shows a slight elevation in the middle, not seen in other 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE0416DCAD1EDC7FEB024A0" authorityName=", Kowalski &amp; Lakes-Harlan" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,258,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hetrodini">Hetrodini</taxonomicName>
species. The calling song consists of a long, uninterrupted trill (song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE0416DCE56EDC0FBF224A3" box="[1040,1088,1196,1222]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
A) with a SRR of about 44 Hz (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE0416DCAE6EDA3FEB7248C" box="[160,261,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[156,1433,260,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-48@14.[151,1436,237,1299]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 10. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Eugaster, Eugasteroides and Spalacomimus (figures of S. liberianus based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Eugaster guyoni, B Eugaster spinulosa, C Eugasteroides loricatus, D Spalacomimus liberianus, E Spalacomimus magnus, F Spalacomimus stettinensis, G Spalacomimus talpa, H Spalacomimus verruciferus, I Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392739/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE0416DCB7AEDA3FE23248C" box="[316,401,1231,1257]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81ED9FFE9B2554" blockId="22.[151,1437,978,1402]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCA81ED9FFE8F2568" bold="true" box="[199,317,1267,1293]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Genitalia.</emphasis>
As in 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE0416DCBCEED98FE5F2568" authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1838" box="[392,493,1268,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eugaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCBCEED98FE5F2568" box="[392,493,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Eugaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we could not find a titillator or other sclerotized genitalic elements despite careful examination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE0416DCA81EC57FAA3251C" blockId="22.[151,1437,978,1402]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE0416DCA81EC57FEC92530" bold="true" box="[199,379,1339,1365]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
